Notes About Pointers

int a; //variable
int *p; //pointer that points to an address of an int type address us 64

p= &a; // this returns a pointer or rather an address of a to the pointer variable p. has an address of 204 say,

a = 5; 

print p : what is the value of p?
204

print &a
204

print &p 
64

print *p
5 //this is called dereferencing

*p = 8

print a
8

//p address
//*p value at address
